During the last month of 2023, our family experienced some tough times, while my husband was in the hospital and my son had severe stomach flu during his final exam week at school. Together with the terrible winter weather we had in L.A. (storms, floods, strong winds) ‚Äî it felt like the sky was falling on me personally. But a real bright spot for me during those times was @hyundaiusa , rain or shine, our Hyundai always makes me feel safe and secure ‚Äî between driving to the hospital, home, school, & grocery stores, I felt I had someone there that always supported me and had my back. Time goes fast, here we almost in March of 2024, and thanks to GOD, my husband is home and getting better every day, and I am truly thankful to be able to partner with @hyundaiUSA again and to share our new adventures in 2024 with you. ‚ù§Ô∏èYes! We are planning road trips again (some to check out college campuses of interest to our son)! And, yes! We are proud to be new #HyundaiTucson drivers .....more to come! Thanks so much for your following.... üíô

A can‚Äôt -miss city to visit this Spring ‚Äî@visitcarlsbad !

Recall some of our last visit highlights, and we have some recommendations for you if you are planning your Carlsbad trip for Spring.

1.The Flower Fields is opening on March 1st. If you like flowers and nature, @The_flower_fields is the place you don‚Äôt want to miss when in the area.

2.There are a couple hotels we stay in and really love.
a.@omnilacosta is a very beautiful hotel & also is a significant resort that it is a member of the Historic Hotels of America, part of the National Trust for Historic Preservation.
b.@Grandpacpal is a hotel right next to the Flower Fields, and you will have the whole flower field as your backyard when staying there ‚Äî imagine that!
c.@legolandcalifornia hotel. ‚Äî it‚Äôs heaven for a family with children, kids LOVE it! Parents, too! üòÉ

3.Places where we love to dine in Carlsbad:
a. @bobs_steakandchop house that is located in the @omnilacosta
b.@caserotacos ‚Äî Best Mexican food we have tasted...our whole family agreed on this one!

4.There are also endless other activities offered in Carlsbad. I like my morning yoga in the flower fields, and my husband enjoyed his relaxing pool time, and my son can‚Äôt wait to go back for his @k1speed car racing with his friend. You can always find something fun to do there, and the weather will never disappoint you!
